The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Cop accused of boy assault
                                                                                                               Cop accused of boy assault
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A 15-year-old boy, caught sneaking out of Salt Lake stadium with iron rods, was tied to a tree trunk and beaten up allegedly by a constable and guards of the sports complex. The boy was later arrested but no action was taken against those who assaulted him.        
	According to witnesses, a constable of Bidhannagar South police station joined the guards in punching the minor before his seniors arrived at the spot.         
	The boy was treated before being arrested. He will be produced in the juvenile court on Friday, said Debabrata Das, the additional superintendent of Bidhannagar police. He added that the cops were probing the role of the constable.        
	Arms plane leaves: The United Arab Emirates air force plane that was being detained at Calcutta airport since September 6 for carrying undeclared arms and explosives took off from the city at 9.23am on Thursday after obtaining clearances from the ministries of external affairs and defence. The flight is scheduled to land in Calcutta again for refuelling on September 17 on its way back to Abu Dhabi from Hanyang in China.        
	Chicago Day: Ramakrishna Mission Swami Vivekanandas Ancestral House and Cultural Centre will celebrate Chicago Day on September 11 and 12 to commemorate the lecture delivered by Swami Vivekananda at The Parliament of Religion in Chicago in 1893. The celebration will be inaugurated at 5pm on Friday. A youth convention will start at 9am on Saturday.         
	Woman run over: A 34-year-old woman was run over by an unidentified vehicle on the EM Bypass, near the Paroma rotary, on Thursday evening. Police said Chaya Ghosh, a Chingrihata resident, was hit from behind while crossing the road. She was declared dead at Chittaranjan hospital.        
	Molest teacher: Calcutta University on Thursday asked Indubhusan Mondal, a teacher of Viharilal College of Home and Social Sciences who had allegedly molested a postgraduate student in 2007, to go on leave till departmental proceedings against him are over.        
	Metro disruption: Metro Railway trains were disrupted for around 15 minutes around noon on Thursday when a 50-year-old man tried to commit suicide at Central station. The man was rescued.                                                                                                                                                                           
